"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.drink.body" = "Lightly sweet Moscato or late-harvest white complements the caramel and vanilla without overwhelming the custard. A small pour of Tawny-style dessert wine also fits the caramel notes. For a non-alcoholic option, serve espresso or strong black coffee, or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.drink.summary" = "Dessert wine (Moscato)";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.info" = "Argentine flan is a silky baked caramel custard, unmolded so the amber caramel becomes its sauce. In Argentina it’s often served as flan mixto, topped with dulce de leche and a spoon of whipped cream, making it a classic restaurant and home dessert enjoyed after asado or a family meal.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.info.summary" = "Flan with dulce de leche";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.name" = "Flan with dulce de leche";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step1.body" = "Preheat the oven and place the flan mold inside a roasting pan so it is ready for the bain-marie.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step1.title" = "Preheat and set up";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step10.body" = "Whip %i9 with %i10 until softly thick and spoonable.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step10.title" = "Whip the cream";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step11.body" = "Loosen the edges with a knife, invert onto a plate so the caramel runs over the flan, then serve topped with %i8 and a spoon of whipped cream.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step11.title" = "Unmold and serve";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step2.body" = "Cook %i1 with a little %i2 in a saucepan until it turns deep amber, swirling as needed for even color.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step2.title" = "Make the caramel";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step3.body" = "Immediately pour the hot caramel into the mold and tilt to coat the base evenly, then let it set.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step3.title" = "Coat the mold";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step4.body" = "Heat %i3 until steaming but not boiling, then remove from the heat.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step4.title" = "Warm the milk";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step5.body" = "Whisk %i4, %i5, %i6, and %i7 until combined, then slowly whisk in the warm milk to avoid curdling.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step5.title" = "Mix the custard";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step6.body" = "Strain the custard through a fine sieve into the caramel-lined mold to ensure a smooth texture.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step6.title" = "Strain into the mold";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step7.body" = "Pour boiling %i11 into the roasting pan around the mold to create a bain-marie, taking care not to splash into the custard.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step7.title" = "Add boiling water";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step8.body" = "Bake until the flan is set around the edges with a slight wobble in the center.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step8.title" = "Bake gently";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step9.body" = "Remove the mold from the water bath and cool, then refrigerate until fully chilled and firm.";
"recipe.ar_flan_con_dulce_de_leche.step9.title" = "Cool completely";
