"recipe.ar_humita_en_chala.info" = "Humita en chala is a traditional Argentine-Andean preparation of fresh corn cooked into a creamy, savory-sweet mash with sautéed onion, milk, and warm spices, then wrapped in corn husks, tied, and steamed until set. Typically enjoyed hot as a comforting meal, each parcel is opened at the table and eaten straight from the husk, often with a soft, melty center of fresh cheese.";
