"recipe.ar_provoleta.info" = "Provoleta is a classic Argentine asado starter: a thick round of provolone is grilled until bubbling and browned, then finished with oregano and chili flakes and eaten hot with crusty bread. Served straight from the grill pan, it’s meant to be shared at the start of a parrillada while the meats cook.";
