"recipe.ar_queso_y_dulce.drink.body" = "A lightly sweet Moscato complements the quince’s floral sweetness and the salty cheese, while a small pour of sparkling wine also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve espresso or strong black coffee, or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.ar_queso_y_dulce.drink.summary" = "Dessert wine (Moscato)";
"recipe.ar_queso_y_dulce.info" = "Queso y dulce is a traditional Argentine dessert of a firm fresh cheese served with sweet fruit paste, most famously quince paste, known as vigilante. It’s a simple, classic finish to a meal, enjoyed in homes and bodegones, where the salty, milky cheese contrasts with the dense, fragrant sweetness of the dulce.";
