"recipe.at_apfelstrudel.info" = "Apfelstrudel is a traditional Austrian strudel made with a thin, hand-stretched dough wrapped around a fragrant filling of tart apples, rum-soaked raisins, cinnamon, and buttery toasted breadcrumbs. Baked until crisp and golden, it is served warm and dusted with sugar, classically accompanied by vanilla sauce that pools around the slices.";
