"recipe.at_backhendl.info" = "Wiener Backhendl is a traditional Austrian dish of chicken pieces seasoned, coated in flour, egg, and breadcrumbs, then fried until crisp and golden. It is classically served with a light potato and lamb’s lettuce salad dressed with vinegar and oil, which cuts through the rich fried crust.";
