"recipe.at_frittatensuppe.info" = "Frittatensuppe is a traditional Austrian starter of clear beef broth served with thin crêpe strips (Frittaten) cut into ribbons. The pancakes are cooked plainly, sliced finely, and added at the last moment so they soften slightly but keep their shape in the hot broth.";
