"recipe.be_carbonnade_flamande.drink.body" = "Pair with a Belgian oud bruin or dubbel that echoes the stew’s malty sweetness and gentle tang. A medium-bodied red like Pinot Noir can also work with the caramelized onions and beef. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water or a malty alcohol-free dark beer to match the stew’s depth.";
"recipe.be_carbonnade_flamande.drink.summary" = "Beer (Belgian)";
"recipe.be_carbonnade_flamande.info" = "Carbonnade flamande (stoofvlees) is a classic Belgian beef-and-onion stew slowly braised in dark Belgian beer until the meat turns fork-tender and the sauce becomes glossy and deep. A slice of mustard-spread gingerbread melts into the pot to thicken the gravy and give its signature sweet-sour balance. Traditionally it is served piping hot with Belgian frites and mayonnaise.";
"recipe.be_carbonnade_flamande.info.summary" = "Beer-braised beef classic";
