"recipe.be_paling_in_t_groen.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, high-acid dry white such as Muscadet or Sauvignon Blanc, or enjoy a gueuze or other tart lambic-style beer that echoes the dish’s bright herbal tang. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or a tart alcohol-free apple drink.";
"recipe.be_paling_in_t_groen.drink.summary" = "White wine (Muscadet)";
"recipe.be_paling_in_t_groen.info" = "Paling in 't groen is a traditional Flemish dish of freshwater eel gently cooked in a vivid green herb sauce. The sauce is built from aromatics, butter and a light thickener, then finished with a generous mix of fresh herbs and a touch of lemon for a bright, slightly tangy balance. It is typically served hot with Belgian frites and mayonnaise to soak up the fragrant green sauce.";
