"recipe.be_vol_au_vent.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp dry white such as Chardonnay or Sauvignon Blanc to balance the creamy sauce, or a Belgian blond ale for a brasserie-style match. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or an alcohol-free blond beer.";
"recipe.be_vol_au_vent.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.be_vol_au_vent.info" = "Belgian vol-au-vent is a classic brasserie dish of crisp puff pastry cases filled with tender poached chicken, mushrooms, and small meatballs in a rich velouté-style sauce finished with cream and egg yolk. It is traditionally served hot with Belgian frites and mayonnaise, making it a comforting, hearty plate found across Belgium.";
