"recipe.be_waterzooi.drink.body" = "Pair with a dry, medium-bodied white such as Chardonnay or Pinot Blanc to match the creamy liaison and delicate chicken broth. A Belgian blond ale also pairs well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or a light, alcohol-free wheat beer.";
"recipe.be_waterzooi.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.be_waterzooi.info" = "Waterzooi is a traditional Belgian dish from Ghent: chicken gently simmered with aromatic vegetables to make a light broth, then finished with a rich liaison of egg yolk and cream for a silky, pale sauce. It is served hot with tender vegetables and chicken in the creamy broth, traditionally accompanied by boiled potatoes that are eaten alongside or added to the bowl.";
"recipe.be_waterzooi.info.summary" = "Ghent creamy chicken stew";
