"recipe.bo_chairo.drink.body" = "A light young red wine such as Pinot Noir works well with the earthy chuño, meat, and vegetables without overpowering the broth. A pale lager is also a good match. For a non-alcoholic option, serve hot herbal tea or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.bo_chairo.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.bo_chairo.info" = "Chairo is a traditional Bolivian highland soup, especially associated with La Paz, made with beef, lamb, chuño, wheat, and a mix of vegetables simmered into a hearty and restorative broth. It is served hot as a substantial family meal, especially in cold weather, and is traditionally finished with fresh herbs.";
"recipe.bo_chairo.info.summary" = "Andean chuño soup";
