"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.drink.body" = "A cold light lager pairs very well with the rich peanut broth and beef. A soft young red wine can also work with the soup’s savory depth. For a non-alcoholic option, serve mocochinchi or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.drink.summary" = "Beer (Lager)";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.info" = "Sopa de Mani is a traditional Bolivian peanut soup, especially associated with the Andean regions, made from beef, ground peanuts, vegetables, and a rich broth finished with fried potato strips and herbs. It is served hot as a hearty family meal and is commonly accompanied by llajua and bread.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.info.summary" = "Peanut beef soup";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.name" = "Peanut soup";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step1.body" = "Cut %i1 into serving pieces if needed. Finely chop %i3, mince %i4, dice %i5 and %i6, chop %i15 and %i18, peel %i7, and separate about half the potatoes for frying and the rest for the soup.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step1.title" = "Prepare the ingredients";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step2.body" = "Soak %i2 briefly in warm water, then blend them with a little %i14 until smooth and creamy.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step2.title" = "Blend the peanuts";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step3.body" = "Heat part of %i10 in the large pot and brown the beef well on all sides. Season with part of %i12 and %i13.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step3.title" = "Brown the beef";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step4.body" = "Add the onion, garlic, carrot, and bell pepper to the pot and cook until softened. Stir in %i11 and cook until fragrant.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step4.title" = "Make the base";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step5.body" = "Add the blended peanuts, the potatoes for the soup, %i9, and water. Bring to a boil, lower the heat, and simmer until the beef is tender and the soup has thickened.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step5.title" = "Simmer the broth";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step6.body" = "Stir in %i8 and cook until tender. Taste and adjust the salt, then keep the soup hot over low heat.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step6.title" = "Add peas and adjust the soup";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step7.body" = "Cut the remaining potatoes into thin strips. Heat the rest of the oil in the skillet and fry the potatoes until golden and crisp, then drain well.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step7.title" = "Fry the potato strips";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step8.body" = "Blend %i16, %i17, cilantro, and %i19 until the sauce is coarse and bright. Set it aside for serving.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step8.title" = "Make the llajua";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step9.body" = "Ladle the sopa de mani into bowls and top with fried potato strips and parsley. Serve hot with llajua and %i20 on the side.";
"recipe.bo_sopa_de_mani.step9.title" = "Serve traditionally";
