"recipe.ca_rappie_pie.info" = "Rappie Pie is a traditional Acadian dish from southwestern Nova Scotia made by grating potatoes, removing their liquid, and replacing it with hot chicken broth before baking around chicken and onion. It is a hearty family and special-occasion dish, traditionally served hot with extra broth spooned over each portion.";
