"recipe.cl_pastel_de_jaiba.drink.body" = "Pair with an unoaked Chilean Chardonnay or a crisp Sauvignon Blanc to match the crab and balance the richness of cream and cheese. A light, dry sparkling wine also works well. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon or a chilled citrus-ginger drink.";
"recipe.cl_pastel_de_jaiba.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.cl_pastel_de_jaiba.info" = "Pastel de jaiba is a traditional Chilean coastal casserole made by sautéing onion and garlic with ají de color and oregano, then folding in sweet crab meat and white wine before thickening the mixture with bread soaked in milk. It is enriched with butter, finished with cream, topped with grated cheese, and baked in small dishes until bubbling and deeply golden. Served hot straight from the oven, it is a classic seafood specialty along Chile’s coast.";
