"recipe.cl_porotos_granados.info" = "Porotos granados is a traditional Chilean summer stew made with fresh cranberry beans cooked with squash, corn, and a seasoned onion-garlic base, thickened with a little mashed squash and often finished with a basil-infused corn mixture for aroma. It is served hot in bowls as a hearty meatless main, showcasing peak-season beans and sweet corn.";
