"recipe.cn_chongqing_huo_guo.drink.body" = "A crisp lager or light wheat beer helps cool the heat and cleans the palate, while chilled unsweetened barley tea is a classic non-alcoholic option for balancing the rich spicy broth.";
"recipe.cn_chongqing_huo_guo.drink.summary" = "Beer (Lager)";
"recipe.cn_chongqing_huo_guo.info" = "Chongqing hot pot is a traditional communal Chinese meal built around a deeply spicy and numbing mala broth made with beef tallow, dried chilies, Sichuan peppercorns, fermented bean pastes, and aromatics. It is served simmering at the table with thin-sliced meats, offal, tofu, vegetables, and noodles cooked by diners and eaten with a simple oil-garlic dipping sauce.";
