"recipe.co_ajiaco.drink.body" = "Pair with an unoaked Chardonnay or a crisp Sauvignon Blanc to complement the chicken broth and potatoes without overpowering the guascas. A light wheat beer also fits well. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lime or a cold lemonade with little sweetness.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.info" = "Ajiaco Santafereño is Bogotá’s traditional chicken and potato soup, built on a long-simmered broth with chicken and corn on the cob, thickened with a trio of potatoes and perfumed with guascas. It is served steaming hot with classic accompaniments at the table: white rice, avocado, capers, and cream, so each bowl can be finished to taste while keeping the soup’s distinctive herbal aroma and creamy texture.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.info.summary" = "Bogotá chicken soup";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.name" = "Ajiaco";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step1.body" = "Wash and cut %i3, peel %i4, and separate %i5 stems from leaves. Peel and cut %i9 and %i10 into chunks, keeping %i11 whole.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step1.title" = "Prep ingredients";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step2.body" = "Add %i1, %i2, scallions, garlic, cilantro stems, %i7, %i8, and %i6 to a large pot. Bring to a gentle simmer, skim any foam, cover partially, and cook until the chicken is tender and the broth is flavorful.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step2.title" = "Simmer the broth";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step3.body" = "Remove the chicken and let it cool slightly, then shred into bite-sized pieces. Keep it covered so it stays moist.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step3.title" = "Shred the chicken";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step4.body" = "Return the broth to a steady simmer and add russet and yukon gold potatoes. Cook until they begin to break down and the soup naturally thickens.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step4.title" = "Thicken with potatoes";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step5.body" = "Add baby yellow potatoes and stir in %i12. Simmer until the baby potatoes are tender and the soup has the characteristic herbal aroma.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step5.title" = "Add baby potatoes and guascas";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step6.body" = "Return shredded chicken to the pot and warm through. Taste and adjust salt, then remove corn pieces for serving.";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step6.title" = "Finish the soup";
"recipe.co_ajiaco.step7.body" = "Cook %i13 until tender and fluffy, then keep it warm for serving.";
