"recipe.co_sancocho.drink.body" = "Pair with an unoaked Chardonnay or a crisp Sauvignon Blanc that won’t fight the herbal cilantro finish. A light lager also pairs well with the hearty broth. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lime or a cold agua de panela with lemon.";
"recipe.co_sancocho.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.co_sancocho.info" = "Colombian sancocho is a traditional one-pot soup built on a long-simmered broth with meat on the bone and starchy roots like yuca and plantain, plus potatoes and corn on the cob for body and sweetness. It is finished with cilantro and served hot with white rice and avocado on the side, a classic weekend family meal across Colombia.";
"recipe.co_sancocho.info.summary" = "Weekend sancocho";
"recipe.co_sancocho.name" = "Sancocho";
