"recipe.co_sobrebarriga.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied Tempranillo or young Malbec that complements the savory tomato sauce and rich braised beef. A crisp lager also works well. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lime or a cold agua de panela with lemon.";
"recipe.co_sobrebarriga.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Tempranillo)";
"recipe.co_sobrebarriga.info" = "Sobrebarriga en salsa is a traditional Colombian braise of beef flank simmered slowly with aromatics until very tender, then finished in a tomato-onion sauce that coats the meat. It is typically served hot with white rice and boiled potatoes, often with avocado on the side, making a classic home-style main dish.";
"recipe.co_sobrebarriga.info.summary" = "Braised flank in sauce";
"recipe.co_sobrebarriga.name" = "Beef in sauce";
