"recipe.cu_yuca_con_mojo.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, citrusy white such as Albariño or Sauvignon Blanc to match the mojo and cut through the olive oil. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lime or a tart citrus juice.";
"recipe.cu_yuca_con_mojo.drink.summary" = "White wine (Albariño)";
"recipe.cu_yuca_con_mojo.info" = "Cuban yuca con mojo is tender boiled cassava dressed with a warm garlic-citrus sauce made with sour orange and olive oil, often with softened onions. It is served hot or warm as a classic side on Cuban tables, especially alongside roast pork and other festive dishes, with the bright mojo soaking into the yuca.";
"recipe.cu_yuca_con_mojo.info.summary" = "Garlicky mojo yuca";
