"recipe.de_maultaschen.drink.body" = "Pair with a dry white such as Silvaner or Pinot Blanc that complements herbs and broth without overpowering the dish. A mild German lager also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water or a warm herbal tea.";
"recipe.de_maultaschen.drink.summary" = "White wine (Silvaner)";
"recipe.de_maultaschen.info" = "Maultaschen are traditional large pasta pockets from Swabia, filled with a savory mixture of minced meat, spinach, onions, herbs, and soaked bread, then simmered gently in broth. The classic serving is in clear beef broth as a soup course or light main, where the dumpling-like pockets stay tender and the filling remains juicy.";
