"recipe.de_rote_gruetze.info" = "Rote Grütze is a traditional northern German dessert of mixed red berries gently cooked and thickened with starch to a glossy, spoonable pudding. It is chilled until set and classically served with a smooth vanilla sauce, which balances the tart fruit with creamy sweetness. It is a staple summer dessert when berries are at their best.";
"recipe.de_rote_gruetze.info.summary" = "North German berry bowl";
