"recipe.dz_bourek.drink.body" = "A light, fruity red such as Gamay works well with the warm spices and fried pastry without feeling heavy. A dry, crisp rosé is also a good match. Non-alcoholic pairing: mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.dz_bourek.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Gamay)";
"recipe.dz_bourek.info" = "Algerian bourek are crisp, golden pastry rolls made with dioul (malsouka) sheets wrapped around a savory minced-meat filling scented with onion, garlic, herbs, and warm spices, then fried until shatteringly crisp. They are a signature Ramadan starter in Algeria and are traditionally served alongside a bowl of chorba frik, making a comforting and festive beginning to the meal.";
"recipe.dz_bourek.info.summary" = "Algerian meat pastries";
