"recipe.dz_chakhchoukha.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied red such as Syrah pairs well with the spiced tomato stew and lamb without overpowering the dish. If you prefer white, choose a fuller, aromatic white like Viognier. Non-alcoholic pairing: mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.dz_chakhchoukha.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.dz_chakhchoukha.info" = "Chakhchoukha is a traditional Algerian dish where thin semolina flatbread (rougag) is cooked, steamed until tender, then torn and mixed with a rich tomato-based lamb stew studded with chickpeas and vegetables, perfumed with warm North African spices. It is served as a hearty communal main, with the sauce thoroughly coating the bread so every bite is savory, fragrant, and comforting.";
"recipe.dz_chakhchoukha.info.summary" = "Bread-softened stew";
"recipe.dz_chakhchoukha.name" = "Chakhchoukha";
