"recipe.dz_chorba_beida.drink.body" = "A crisp, dry white like Vermentino pairs well with the lemony finish and delicate chicken broth. A light-bodied red served slightly cool can also work if you prefer red. Non-alcoholic pairing: hot mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.dz_chorba_beida.drink.summary" = "White wine (Vermentino)";
"recipe.dz_chorba_beida.info" = "Chorba Beida is a traditional Algerian white soup made with chicken simmered in a clear, gently spiced broth, finished with vermicelli and a silky egg-and-lemon liaison that gives the soup its characteristic pale color and comforting richness. It is commonly served as a warming starter, especially during Ramadan, with lemon at the table and homemade Algerian bread to accompany each bowl.";
"recipe.dz_chorba_beida.info.summary" = "White lemon chicken soup";
