"recipe.dz_chtitha_djaj.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied red like Syrah complements the paprika-rich sauce and savory chicken while handling gentle heat. If you prefer white, choose a fuller, aromatic white such as Viognier. Non-alcoholic pairing: mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.dz_chtitha_djaj.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.dz_chtitha_djaj.info" = "Chtitha Djaj is a traditional Algerian chicken stew simmered in a rich, spicy red sauce built from tomatoes, garlic, and a generous amount of paprika and hot pepper, finished with chickpeas and a drizzle of olive oil. It is served as a hearty main, commonly accompanied by traditional Algerian bread to scoop up the thick, peppery sauce.";
