"recipe.eg_hamam_mahshi.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied red such as Grenache or a fruity Syrah that matches the roasted flavors and warm spices. A crisp lager also works well with the rich, savory pigeon and freekeh. Non-alcoholic option: mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.eg_hamam_mahshi.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Grenache)";
"recipe.eg_hamam_mahshi.info" = "Hamam mahshi is a traditional Egyptian celebratory dish of whole pigeons stuffed with freekeh, then gently simmered until tender and finished by roasting to a deep golden brown. The nutty freekeh absorbs the aromatic juices while the skin turns crisp and savory, making it a prized centerpiece for family feasts and special occasions served piping hot.";
"recipe.eg_hamam_mahshi.info.summary" = "Stuffed roast pigeon";
"recipe.eg_hamam_mahshi.name" = "Stuffed pigeon";
