"recipe.eg_kebda_iskandarani.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, high-acid dry white such as Sauvignon Blanc to match the garlic, vinegar, and chile while refreshing the palate. A light lager also works well with the spicy, savory sandwich. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.eg_kebda_iskandarani.drink.summary" = "White wine (Sauvignon)";
"recipe.eg_kebda_iskandarani.info" = "Kebda iskandarani is Alexandria’s famous street-food liver, quickly sautéed with plenty of garlic, green pepper, and hot chile, then sharpened with vinegar and lemon. The liver stays tender while the sauce turns punchy and aromatic with cumin and coriander, and it is traditionally served immediately as sandwiches in baladi bread with tahini and pickled turnips.";
"recipe.eg_kebda_iskandarani.info.summary" = "Alexandrian liver sandwich";
"recipe.eg_kebda_iskandarani.name" = "Alexandrian liver";
