"recipe.eg_kofta.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied red such as Grenache or a fruity Syrah that matches the charred spices and rich meat. A crisp lager also works well with grilled kebabs. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon or mint tea.";
"recipe.eg_kofta.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Grenache)";
"recipe.eg_kofta.info" = "Egyptian kofta are spiced minced-meat kebabs shaped onto skewers and grilled until smoky and juicy, typically made with beef or a beef-lamb mix and plenty of onion and parsley. They are traditionally served hot with baladi bread, grilled onion and tomatoes, and a tangy tahini sauce thinned with lemon and garlic, making a classic street-food and family-meal centerpiece.";
"recipe.eg_kofta.info.summary" = "Charcoal kofta skewers";
