"recipe.eg_koshari.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, high-acid dry white such as Sauvignon Blanc to lift the tomato and vinegar and cut through the fried onions. A light lager also works well with the hearty, savory bowl. Non-alcoholic option: mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.eg_koshari.drink.summary" = "White wine (Sauvignon)";
"recipe.eg_koshari.info" = "Koshari is Egypt’s beloved street-food bowl of layered rice, lentils, and pasta topped with spiced tomato sauce, crisp fried onions, and a sharp garlic-vinegar daqqa. Served hot and mixed at the table, it balances hearty grains and legumes with tangy sauce and crunchy onions, and is traditionally eaten with a spoon alongside simple bread.";
"recipe.eg_koshari.info.summary" = "Street-food lentil bowl";
"recipe.eg_koshari.name" = "Koshari";
