"recipe.eg_om_ali.drink.body" = "Pair with an aromatic sweet wine such as Moscato or a late-harvest Riesling to match the warm dairy sweetness and toasted nuts. A small glass of sweet sherry also complements the caramelized top. Non-alcoholic option: mint tea or Arabic coffee.";
"recipe.eg_om_ali.drink.summary" = "Sweet wine (Moscato)";
"recipe.eg_om_ali.info" = "Om Ali is a traditional Egyptian baked milk dessert made by layering crisp baked pastry with nuts, raisins, and coconut, then soaking it with sweetened milk and cream and baking until bubbling and golden on top. Served warm straight from the dish, it’s a comforting classic associated with family gatherings and festive meals, prized for its creamy custard-like base and toasted crunchy surface.";
