"recipe.eg_roz_bel_laban.drink.body" = "Pair with an aromatic sweet wine such as Moscato or late-harvest Riesling to complement the milky sweetness. A small glass of sweet sherry also works well with the creamy texture. Non-alcoholic option: mint tea or Arabic coffee.";
"recipe.eg_roz_bel_laban.drink.summary" = "Sweet wine (Moscato)";
"recipe.eg_roz_bel_laban.info" = "Roz bel laban is a classic Egyptian rice pudding simmered slowly in milk until the rice turns tender and the mixture becomes thick and creamy, lightly sweetened and scented with vanilla. Served chilled or at cool room temperature, it is a comforting everyday dessert across Egypt, often finished with a sprinkle of nuts.";
