"recipe.eg_sayadeya.drink.summary" = "White wine (Sauvignon)";
"recipe.eg_sayadeya.info" = "Sayadeya is a traditional Egyptian coastal dish of deeply caramelized onions cooked into a fragrant, brown-tinted rice made with fish stock and warm spices, served with fried fish on top. The onions give the rice its signature savory sweetness and color, while the fish stays crisp and tender. It is commonly served hot with a tangy tahini sauce to balance the richness.";
"recipe.eg_sayadeya.info.summary" = "Fish over onion rice";
