"recipe.eg_shorbet_ads.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, high-acid dry white such as Sauvignon Blanc to lift the cumin and lemon and cut through the soup’s warmth. A light lager also works well with the savory lentils. Non-alcoholic option: mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.eg_shorbet_ads.drink.summary" = "White wine (Sauvignon)";
"recipe.eg_shorbet_ads.info" = "Shorbet ads is a classic Egyptian red lentil soup simmered with onion, garlic, and carrot, then blended into a smooth, warming bowl seasoned with cumin, coriander, and turmeric. It is served hot as a comforting starter or light meal, traditionally with baladi bread for dipping and lemon to brighten the earthy lentils.";
