"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied Spanish red such as Rioja Crianza to complement the rich pork and crisp skin without overpowering. A dry sparkling Cava also works well to cut through the fat. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Rioja Crianza)";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.info" = "Cochinillo asado is the famed Segovian roast of young suckling pig, seasoned simply with salt and roasted over WATER until the meat is meltingly tender and the skin turns deeply crisp and blistered. Served hot with its pan juices and crusty bread for dipping, it’s a celebratory Castilian classic associated with Segovia’s roasting traditions and shared at the table as a centerpiece dish.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.info.summary" = "Segovia roast suckling pig";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.name" = "Roast suckling pig";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step1.body" = "Heat the oven. Pat %i1 dry and score the skin lightly without cutting into the meat. Season the pig thoroughly with %i2, including folds and joints.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step1.title" = "Prepare the pig and oven";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step2.body" = "Place the pig on a rack set over a roasting tray and pour %i3 into the tray. Roast until the meat is tender and the fat has rendered well, keeping water in the tray so the drippings do not burn.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step2.title" = "Roast skin-side down";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step3.body" = "Carefully turn the pig skin-side up. Refresh the tray with water if needed and spoon pan juices over the meat side, avoiding the skin.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step3.title" = "Flip and moisten the tray";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step4.body" = "Continue roasting until the meat is fully tender and the skin begins to dry and tighten, maintaining water in the tray as needed.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step4.title" = "Roast until nearly crisp";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step5.body" = "Increase the heat and roast until the skin is deeply blistered and crackling, rotating the tray if necessary for even browning.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step5.title" = "Crisp the skin";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step6.body" = "Remove from the oven and rest so juices settle and the skin stays crisp.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step6.title" = "Rest before carving";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step7.body" = "Carve into portions and serve immediately with pan juices and %i4.";
"recipe.es_cochinillo_asado.step7.title" = "Carve and serve";
