"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, mineral Spanish white such as Txakoli or Albariño to match the briny clams and fresh parsley sauce. A dry Cava also pairs well with the delicate fish and olive oil. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.drink.summary" = "White wine (Txakoli)";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.info" = "Merluza a la vasca is a classic Basque dish of hake gently cooked in a parsley-green sauce built from olive oil, garlic, white wine, and fish stock, traditionally enriched with clams and finished with hard-boiled eggs and tender white asparagus. The sauce is lightly thickened and emulsified so it coats the fish in a silky green sheen, and it is served hot with crusty bread to soak up every spoonful.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.info.summary" = "Basque hake in green";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.name" = "Hake in green sauce";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step1.body" = "Cover %i10 with cold %i11 and let them purge so they release sand. Drain and rinse well.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step1.title" = "Purge the clams";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step2.body" = "Boil %i12 until hard, cool in cold water, peel, and cut into wedges.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step2.title" = "Boil the eggs";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step3.body" = "Finely chop %i8 and slice %i4 thinly so it perfumes the oil without burning.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step3.title" = "Prep parsley and garlic";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step4.body" = "Warm %i3 in a wide pan over low heat and gently cook the garlic until fragrant. Stir in %i5 and cook briefly so it loses its raw taste.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step4.title" = "Start the green sauce base";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step5.body" = "Add %i6 and simmer briefly, then add %i7. Stir in parsley and keep the sauce at a gentle simmer.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step5.title" = "Build the sauce";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step6.body" = "Add clams to the pan, cover, and cook until they open. Lift clams out as they open and strain the cooking liquid through a fine sieve back into the sauce.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step6.title" = "Open the clams";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step7.body" = "Season %i1 with %i2 and add it to the pan in the simmering green sauce. Cover and cook gently, turning carefully once, until just cooked through.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step7.title" = "Cook the hake gently";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step8.body" = "Warm %i13 in the sauce, return the clams, and season with %i9. Serve the hake with clams and asparagus, topped with egg wedges, and %i14 alongside.";
"recipe.es_merluza_a_la_vasca.step8.title" = "Finish with asparagus and garnish";
