"recipe.et_doro_wat.drink.body" = "A light, low-tannin red such as Pinot Noir or a dry rosé complements berbere heat and the buttery, spiced sauce. For a non-alcoholic pairing, serve Ethiopian spiced tea or sparkling water with fresh ginger and lemon.";
"recipe.et_doro_wat.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.et_doro_wat.info" = "Doro Wat is Ethiopia’s iconic chicken and egg wat, built on deeply caramelized onions, berbere spice, and niter kibbeh (spiced clarified butter) for a rich, brick-red sauce. It is traditionally served family-style over injera, the fermented teff flatbread used to scoop the stew, with hard-boiled eggs nestled into the sauce near the end of cooking.";
"recipe.et_doro_wat.info.summary" = "Chicken and egg wat";
