"recipe.et_dulet.info" = "Dulet is a traditional Ethiopian dish of finely chopped tripe, liver, and beef sautéed in niter kibbeh (spiced clarified butter) and seasoned with mitmita and aromatic spices for a bold, warming heat. It is commonly served as part of a shared meal and eaten by scooping with injera, the fermented teff flatbread that also acts as the utensil.";
