"recipe.et_kitfo.info" = "Kitfo is a traditional Ethiopian preparation of finely minced raw beef seasoned with mitmita and niter kibbeh, served warm from the spiced butter but kept essentially raw and tender. It is commonly accompanied by ayib (fresh mild cheese) and gomen (braised collard greens), all eaten by scooping with injera, the fermented teff flatbread.";
