"recipe.et_sambusa.info" = "Sambusa are crisp Ethiopian pastries, traditionally triangular and deep-fried, filled with a savory mixture often made with seasoned legumes during fasting periods. They are commonly served as a starter or snack alongside a berbere-based awaze dipping sauce, meant for sharing and eating by hand.";
