"recipe.gb_shepherds_pie.drink.body" = "A light claret or a malty brown ale pairs well with the rich lamb filling and potato topping. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water or strong black tea.";
"recipe.gb_shepherds_pie.drink.summary" = "Claret";
"recipe.gb_shepherds_pie.info" = "A traditional British shepherd's pie made with minced lamb simmered with onion, carrot, herbs, stock, and Worcestershire sauce, topped with mashed potato and baked until browned. It is a classic family main course served hot, often with green peas.";
