"recipe.gb_steak_and_kidney_pie.drink.body" = "A malty brown ale or a light claret pairs well with the rich gravy and offal. For a non-alcoholic option, serve strong black tea or sparkling water.";
"recipe.gb_steak_and_kidney_pie.drink.summary" = "Beer (Ale)";
"recipe.gb_steak_and_kidney_pie.info" = "A traditional British pie of slow-cooked beef and kidney in a dark onion gravy, topped and lined with shortcrust pastry and baked until golden. It is a classic pub and home-cooked main, served hot with vegetables or potatoes.";
