"recipe.gr_moussaka.drink.body" = "Agiorgitiko (St. George) or a medium-bodied Xinomavro pairs well with the spiced meat and creamy béchamel. A lightly oaked Chardonnay can also work with the richness. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or a chilled, unsweetened iced tea.";
"recipe.gr_moussaka.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Agiorgitiko)";
"recipe.gr_moussaka.info" = "Greek moussaka is a layered oven-baked casserole of potato and eggplant, topped with a cinnamon-scented tomato meat sauce and a thick, egg-enriched béchamel that sets into a creamy golden crust. It’s classic taverna and home comfort food, served in generous slices after it rests, so the layers hold together and the flavors deepen.";
"recipe.gr_moussaka.info.summary" = "Rested taverna moussaka";
