"recipe.gr_papoutsakia.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied Greek red such as Agiorgitiko that complements lamb or beef mince and tomato. A dry rosé also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or a chilled herbal iced tea.";
"recipe.gr_papoutsakia.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Agiorgitiko)";
"recipe.gr_papoutsakia.info" = "Papoutsakia are classic Greek baked eggplants split and roasted, filled with a rich minced meat and tomato sauce, then topped with thick béchamel and baked until golden. They are served hot as a hearty taverna-style main, where the eggplant turns silky and the béchamel forms a browned cap over the savory filling.";
