"recipe.gr_revithada.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp Greek white such as Assyrtiko or Savatiano that stays fresh with olive oil and slow-cooked onion. A light lager also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or a chilled herbal iced tea.";
"recipe.gr_revithada.drink.summary" = "White wine (Assyrtiko)";
"recipe.gr_revithada.info" = "Revithada is a traditional Greek island dish, especially from Sifnos, where chickpeas are baked slowly with onion, bay, and plenty of olive oil until creamy and richly flavored. It is typically started the day before, baked low and slow, and served hot with bread to mop up the thick, golden chickpea broth.";
"recipe.gr_revithada.info.summary" = "Sifnos baked chickpeas";
