"recipe.gr_youvarlakia.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp Greek white such as Assyrtiko that matches lemon and keeps the dish bright. A light lager also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or a chilled lemon soda.";
"recipe.gr_youvarlakia.drink.summary" = "White wine (Assyrtiko)";
"recipe.gr_youvarlakia.info" = "Youvarlakia are traditional Greek meatballs simmered with rice in broth, finished with avgolemono, a silky egg-and-lemon liaison that turns the soup creamy without dairy. The meatballs stay tender, the rice thickens the broth slightly, and the lemony finish is bright and warming. It is served hot as a comforting main, often with bread.";
"recipe.gr_youvarlakia.info.summary" = "Lemony meatball soup";
