"recipe.hk_char_siu_bao.drink.body" = "These buns are usually paired with tea rather than wine, especially jasmine or pu-erh during dim sum. If serving a drink pairing, a light off-dry white can work, while hot jasmine tea is the classic non-alcoholic option.";
"recipe.hk_char_siu_bao.drink.summary" = "Jasmine tea";
"recipe.hk_char_siu_bao.info" = "A traditional Cantonese dim sum bun with a soft white steamed dough and a savory-sweet char siu filling thickened into a glossy sauce. It is commonly served in bamboo steamers during yum cha and eaten hot as part of a shared meal.";
"recipe.hk_char_siu_bao.info.summary" = "Steamed char siu buns";
