"recipe.hu_palacsinta_gundel.info" = "Gundel palacsinta are traditional Hungarian crêpes filled with a sweet walnut-raisin mixture scented with rum and citrus, then folded and served with a warm chocolate sauce, often flambéed. They are served immediately while the sauce is hot and the crêpes are tender, making a classic restaurant dessert associated with Budapest’s Gundel tradition.";
