"recipe.hu_porkolt.info" = "Marhapörkölt is a classic Hungarian beef stew built on slowly softened onions and sweet paprika, then simmered until the beef is tender and the sauce is thick and intensely savory. Unlike goulash soup, it is a dryish stew rather than a broth, and it is traditionally served with nokedli or boiled potatoes to catch the rich paprika gravy.";
"recipe.hu_porkolt.info.summary" = "Paprika beef stew";
"recipe.hu_porkolt.name" = "Beef pörkölt";
