"recipe.hu_somloi_galuska.info" = "Somlói galuska is a classic Hungarian dessert of layered sponge pieces—often vanilla and cocoa—soaked with rum syrup, layered with walnut and raisin filling, then topped with warm chocolate sauce and whipped cream. It is served chilled so the flavors meld and the sponge absorbs the syrup, making a rich, spoonable plated dessert.";
