"recipe.il_hamin.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium- to full-bodied red blend or Syrah that can handle the rich, long-cooked beef and warm spices. For a non-alcoholic option, serve black tea with mint or sparkling water with a squeeze of citrus.";
"recipe.il_hamin.drink.summary" = "Red wine blend";
"recipe.il_hamin.info" = "Hamin is a traditional Israeli Shabbat stew that slow-cooks overnight from before sundown until the next day, developing deep, caramelized flavors. In its classic Sephardi/Mizrahi style it combines beef, chickpeas, eggs in their shells, potatoes, rice, and warm spices, all gently braised until tender and brown. It is served hot for Shabbat lunch, with the eggs and rice traditionally portioned alongside the meat, legumes, and potatoes.";
"recipe.il_hamin.info.summary" = "Overnight Sabbath stew";
"recipe.il_hamin.name" = "Hamin";
"recipe.il_hamin.step1.body" = "Rinse the %i4 and cover with plenty of %i18 in a bowl. Leave to soak at room temperature until fully swollen, then drain.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step1.title" = "Soak the chickpeas";
"recipe.il_hamin.step2.body" = "Heat %i3 in a skillet and brown the %i1 well on all sides. Add chopped %i2 and cook until softened and lightly golden.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step2.title" = "Brown the beef and onions";
"recipe.il_hamin.step3.body" = "Transfer beef and onions to the heavy pot. Add drained chickpeas, whole %i5, %i6, %i12, %i7, %i8, %i9, %i10, and %i11.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step3.title" = "Build the stew base";
"recipe.il_hamin.step4.body" = "Pour in water until everything is well covered. Bring the pot to a gentle simmer, skimming any foam and stirring to dissolve the tomato paste and spices.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step4.title" = "Add water and bring to a simmer";
"recipe.il_hamin.step5.body" = "Gently nestle the %i13, still in their shells, into the stew so they are mostly submerged.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step5.title" = "Add the eggs in shells";
"recipe.il_hamin.step6.body" = "Rinse the %i14 until the water runs clearer, then mix it with %i15, %i16, and %i17. Wrap the rice mixture tightly in parchment paper to form a sealed packet and tie securely with twine.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step6.title" = "Prepare the rice packet";
"recipe.il_hamin.step7.body" = "Set the rice packet on top of the stew so it sits snugly and stays above the heaviest bubbling while still being surrounded by heat and moisture. Cover the pot tightly.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step7.title" = "Place the rice packet in the pot";
"recipe.il_hamin.step8.body" = "Keep the pot at a very low, steady heat so it barely bubbles, and cook slowly overnight until the beef and chickpeas are tender and the stew has darkened and thickened.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step8.title" = "Cook overnight";
"recipe.il_hamin.step9.body" = "Remove the rice packet and let it rest briefly, then open and fluff. Peel the eggs. Serve the beef, chickpeas, potatoes, and broth with portions of rice and an egg for each plate.";
"recipe.il_hamin.step9.title" = "Finish and serve for Shabbat";
