"recipe.iq_masgouf.drink.body" = "A full-bodied white wine such as oak-aged Chardonnay suits the smoky rich fish and tangy tamarind glaze. A light lager also works well. For a non-alcoholic pairing serve strong black tea with fresh lemon or chilled mint lemonade.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.info" = "Masgouf is the classic Iraqi river fish dish made with butterflied carp roasted slowly beside a charcoal fire until smoky outside and succulent inside. It is traditionally served as a shared main course with lemon onion tomato parsley and Iraqi flatbread, especially at riverside restaurants and family meals.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.info.summary" = "Charcoal-roasted carp";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.name" = "Masgouf";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step1.body" = "Scale, gut, and wash %i1, then butterfly it from the back so it opens flat while staying in one piece. Score the thick flesh lightly to help the glaze penetrate and drain the fish well.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step1.title" = "Prepare the carp";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step2.body" = "In a bowl, mix %i2, %i3, %i4, %i5, and %i6 into a thick brushable glaze until smooth.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step2.title" = "Make the tamarind glaze";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step3.body" = "Brush the fish all over with most of the glaze, working it into the cuts and inner flesh. Keep the remaining glaze for basting during cooking.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step3.title" = "Season the fish";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step4.body" = "Prepare a steady charcoal fire and let it burn down until the heat is strong but not aggressively flaming so the fish can roast slowly beside it.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step4.title" = "Light the fire";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step5.body" = "Secure the fish in the rack with the flesh facing the fire and roast it upright until the surface begins to brown and the flesh firms. Baste once or twice with the remaining glaze as it cooks.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step5.title" = "Roast the carp";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step6.body" = "Cut %i7 into wedges, thinly slice %i8, slice %i9, and roughly chop %i10. Warm %i11 near the fire until soft and pliable.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step6.title" = "Prepare the accompaniments";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step7.body" = "Move the fish briefly closer to the coals to char the skin and edges and finish the roasting. Remove it when the flesh flakes easily and the outside is deeply colored.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step7.title" = "Finish over the coals";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step8.body" = "Transfer the fish to a large tray and scatter the onion, tomato, parsley, and lemon around it. Serve immediately with the warm Iraqi flatbread.";
"recipe.iq_masgouf.step8.title" = "Serve the masgouf";
