"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied, savory red such as Syrah or Grenache matches the braised lamb and warm spices without overpowering the herbs and saffron. If you prefer white, choose a textured Chardonnay with moderate oak. Non-alcoholic: doogh (yogurt-mint drink) or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.info" = "Baghali Polo ba Mahicheh is a classic Iranian celebratory dish of fluffy basmati rice layered with dill and fava beans, steamed with a crisp tahdig crust, and served alongside slow-braised lamb shanks in a saffron-scented gravy. It is a centerpiece dish for family gatherings and special occasions, often plated with some plain rice tinted with saffron and spooned with the lamb’s rich sauce.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.info.summary" = "Festive dill rice lamb";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.name" = "Baghali polo";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step1.body" = "Rinse %i12 until the water runs mostly clear, then soak it in salted %i18 so the grains hydrate evenly.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step1.title" = "Soak the rice";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step10.body" = "Wrap the lid with a tea towel, cover tightly, and steam on low heat until the rice is fully cooked, aromatic, and the tahdig is crisp.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step10.title" = "Steam the baghali polo";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step11.body" = "Turn out the rice to reveal the potato tahdig. Plate the lamb shanks alongside and spoon some of the saffron-rich sauce over the meat and rice.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step11.title" = "Serve";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step2.body" = "Slice %i2, mince %i3, and steep %i11 in a little warm water so it releases color and aroma.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step2.title" = "Prep aromatics and saffron";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step3.body" = "Heat %i16 in a heavy pot and brown %i1 well on all sides to develop deep flavor.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step3.title" = "Sear the lamb shanks";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step4.body" = "Add onions to the same pot and cook until softened. Stir in garlic, %i4, %i5, and %i7 and cook until fragrant and slightly darkened.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step4.title" = "Build the braise base";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step5.body" = "Return the shanks to the pot, add %i10, %i8, and %i9, then add enough water to mostly cover. Simmer gently with the lid on until the meat is very tender and the sauce is rich, turning the shanks occasionally.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step5.title" = "Braise until tender";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step6.body" = "Stir the bloomed saffron into the braising liquid and adjust %i6. Keep the shanks warm in their sauce while you make the rice.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step6.title" = "Finish the lamb sauce";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step7.body" = "Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Drain the soaked rice and boil it until the grains are softened on the outside but still firm in the center, then drain well.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step7.title" = "Parboil the rice";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step8.body" = "Slice %i15 and coat the bottom of the rice pot with oil and a little %i17. Arrange the potato slices to cover the base.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step8.title" = "Prepare the tahdig base";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step9.body" = "Mix the parboiled rice with %i14 and %i13 in layers in the pot, building a gentle mound and leaving a few steam vents down to the bottom.";
"recipe.ir_baghali_polo_ba_mahicheh.step9.title" = "Layer rice with dill and beans";
