"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.drink.body" = "A savory, medium-bodied red such as Syrah or Grenache matches the rich herbs, beans, and tender meat. If you prefer white, choose a textured Viognier that can stand up to the stew’s intensity. Non-alcoholic: doogh (yogurt-mint drink) or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.info" = "Ghormeh Sabzi is Iran’s iconic herb stew, built on a deeply fried herb base simmered with tender lamb or beef, kidney beans, and pierced dried limes that give the dish its signature tang and aroma. It is traditionally served as a khoresh alongside fluffy Persian steamed rice, often with a bright saffron finish, and commonly accompanied by torshi at the table.";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.info.summary" = "Iranian herb stew";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.name" = "Ghormeh sabzi";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.step1.body" = "Rinse %i5 and soak them in plenty of %i14 until fully hydrated.";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.step1.title" = "Soak the beans";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.step10.body" = "Bloom crushed %i17 in a little warm water and spoon it over part of the rice. Serve the stew alongside the rice with %i18.";
"recipe.ir_ghormeh_sabzi.step10.title" = "Saffron finish and serve";
