"recipe.ir_sholeh_zard.drink.body" = "Fragrant dessert wines like Muscat or off-dry Riesling complement saffron and rosewater without masking them. If you prefer something richer, a late-harvest Chenin Blanc also works. Non-alcoholic: Persian black tea or chilled rosewater lemonade.";
"recipe.ir_sholeh_zard.drink.summary" = "Sweet wine (Muscat)";
"recipe.ir_sholeh_zard.info" = "Sholeh Zard is a traditional Iranian saffron rice pudding cooked slowly until creamy, then perfumed with rosewater and finished with cinnamon and nuts. It is often prepared for gatherings and religious occasions, portioned into bowls, and decorated with intricate cinnamon patterns once set.";
"recipe.ir_sholeh_zard.info.summary" = "Saffron rice pudding";
"recipe.ir_sholeh_zard.name" = "Sholeh zard";
"recipe.ir_sholeh_zard.step1.body" = "Rinse %i1 until the water runs mostly clear, then soak it in %i2 so the grains soften for even cooking.";
