"recipe.ir_tahchin.drink.body" = "A textured white such as Chardonnay or Viognier pairs well with saffron, yogurt tang, and the rich crust. If you prefer red, choose a light Pinot Noir served slightly cool. Non-alcoholic: doogh (yogurt-mint drink) or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.ir_tahchin.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.ir_tahchin.info" = "Tahchin is a classic Iranian saffron rice “cake” with a crisp golden crust, traditionally made with yogurt, egg yolks, and saffron-coated rice layered around tender chicken. It is unmolded to reveal a deeply browned exterior and served sliced, often with barberries on top and alongside torshi for contrast.";
