"recipe.it_arancini.info" = "Traditional Sicilian arancini are golden, deep-fried rice balls with a creamy saffron rice shell and a savory ragù filling, often with peas and melting cheese at the center. Common as street food and antipasto, they are served hot and crisp right after frying, with the filling rich and the rice tender inside.";
