"recipe.it_ossobuco_alla_milanese.drink.body" = "Pair with a northern Italian red such as Barbera for bright acidity or a lighter-style Nebbiolo to complement the veal and gremolata. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon or a lightly bitter orange soda.";
"recipe.it_ossobuco_alla_milanese.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Barbera)";
"recipe.it_ossobuco_alla_milanese.info" = "A classic Lombard braise of cross-cut veal shanks slowly cooked with soffritto, wine, and broth until meltingly tender, served with the marrow at the bone’s center. Traditionally finished with gremolata and often paired with Risotto alla Milanese, it is a celebratory, comforting dish meant for a long, gentle cook and immediate serving.";
