"recipe.jp_sashimi_moriawase.info" = "Sashimi moriawase is a traditional Japanese assorted sashimi platter featuring a balanced selection of sliced raw fish and seafood arranged with tsuma garnishes such as shredded daikon and shiso. It is commonly served as an appetizer or centerpiece at sushi restaurants, izakaya, and formal meals, with soy sauce, wasabi, and pickled ginger.";
