"recipe.jp_shabu_shabu.info" = "Shabu-shabu is a traditional Japanese nabemono hot pot in which thinly sliced beef and vegetables are briefly swished in a light kombu broth and eaten with dipping sauces. It is commonly served as a shared table meal, especially in cooler seasons, with tofu, mushrooms, greens, and noodles cooked in the pot as the meal progresses.";
