"recipe.kh_beef_lok_lak.drink.body" = "A light fruity red such as Gamay or Pinot Noir works well with the peppery beef and lime sauce. Beer also pairs nicely, especially a pale lager. For a non-alcoholic option, serve iced jasmine tea with lime.";
"recipe.kh_beef_lok_lak.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Gamay)";
"recipe.kh_beef_lok_lak.info" = "Beef lok lak is a classic Cambodian main dish of quickly seared marinated beef served with a fresh salad plate, steamed rice, and a sharp lime-pepper dipping sauce. It is commonly eaten as a lunch or dinner dish and balances savory, sour, and peppery flavors with crisp vegetables.";
"recipe.kh_beef_lok_lak.info.summary" = "Pepper beef plate";
"recipe.kh_beef_lok_lak.name" = "Beef lok lak";
