"recipe.kh_prahok_ktis.drink.body" = "An aromatic white wine such as Riesling pairs well with the salty fermented depth and creamy coconut. A light lager also works with the vegetable platter. For a non-alcoholic option, serve iced jasmine tea or chilled lime water.";
"recipe.kh_prahok_ktis.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.kh_prahok_ktis.info" = "Prahok ktis is a traditional Cambodian coconut-based dip made with prahok, minced pork, aromatics, and coconut milk, gently cooked until rich and savory. It is typically served as a shared starter or side with a platter of fresh and lightly blanched vegetables, and sometimes steamed rice.";
"recipe.kh_prahok_ktis.info.summary" = "Coconut prahok dip";
