"recipe.kr_bibimbap.drink.body" = "A light fruity red such as Gamay or a soft Pinot Noir works well with the savory beef and spicy gochujang sauce. A crisp lager is also a good match. Non-alcoholic pairing: cold barley tea.";
"recipe.kr_bibimbap.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Gamay)";
"recipe.kr_bibimbap.info" = "Bibimbap is a traditional Korean rice dish of steamed rice topped with separately seasoned vegetables, beef, and egg, then mixed at the table with a gochujang-based sauce. It is commonly served as a complete home meal and highlights balance of color, texture, and flavor.";
