"recipe.lb_kibbeh_nayyeh.drink.body" = "Pair with a light, fresh red such as Cinsault or a young Beaujolais-style wine to complement the spices without overpowering the delicate raw meat. For a non-alcoholic option, serve chilled laban or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.lb_kibbeh_nayyeh.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Cinsault)";
"recipe.lb_kibbeh_nayyeh.info" = "Kibbeh nayyeh is the iconic Lebanese raw kibbeh: very fresh, lean meat kneaded until silky with soaked fine bulgur, onion, and kamouneh spices. It is traditionally served as a mezze spread on a plate, finished with olive oil, and eaten immediately with pita, mint, green onions, and radishes.";
"recipe.lb_kibbeh_nayyeh.info.summary" = "Raw kibbeh mezze";
