"recipe.lb_shish_tawook.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp, aromatic white such as Sauvignon Blanc or dry Riesling to complement the lemony marinade and grilled flavors. For a non-alcoholic option, serve laban or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.lb_shish_tawook.drink.summary" = "White wine (Sauvignon)";
"recipe.lb_shish_tawook.info" = "Lebanese shish tawook is a classic grilled chicken skewer dish marinated in garlic, lemon, and yogurt with warm spices, then char-grilled until juicy. It is traditionally served hot with toum garlic sauce and warm pita bread, often alongside grilled vegetables and pickles as part of a Lebanese grill spread.";
"recipe.lb_shish_tawook.info.summary" = "Yogurt-marinated skewers";
