"recipe.lk_fish_ambul_thiyal.drink.body" = "A crisp lager works well with the sharp goraka sourness and peppery spice, while a dry Riesling can also pair nicely. For a non-alcoholic option, serve hot Ceylon tea or plain warm water.";
"recipe.lk_fish_ambul_thiyal.drink.summary" = "Beer (Lager)";
"recipe.lk_fish_ambul_thiyal.info" = "Fish ambul thiyal is a traditional Sri Lankan sour fish curry, usually made with firm tuna and cooked down with goraka, black pepper, curry leaves, and spices until the fish is deeply seasoned and the curry turns almost dry. It is commonly served as a rice accompaniment and is valued for its bold sour flavor and keeping quality.";
"recipe.lk_fish_ambul_thiyal.info.summary" = "Sour black fish curry";
