"recipe.lk_meekiri_with_kithul_pani.drink.body" = "Hot Ceylon tea pairs well with the cool creamy curd and caramel notes of kithul treacle, while a lightly sweet Moscato can work in small servings. For a non-alcoholic option, serve plain hot Ceylon tea or water.";
"recipe.lk_meekiri_with_kithul_pani.drink.summary" = "Tea (Ceylon tea)";
"recipe.lk_meekiri_with_kithul_pani.info" = "Meekiri with kithul pani is a traditional Sri Lankan dessert of thick buffalo curd served with kithul palm treacle poured over the top. It is commonly enjoyed as a simple finish to a meal and is especially associated with southern Sri Lanka.";
