"recipe.lk_polos_curry.drink.body" = "A light red such as Gamay or a dry rosé can work with the spice and coconut richness, and a light lager is also a good match. For a non-alcoholic option, serve plain tea or chilled lime water.";
"recipe.lk_polos_curry.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Gamay)";
"recipe.lk_polos_curry.info" = "Polos curry is a traditional Sri Lankan curry made with young green jackfruit slowly simmered with roasted spices, aromatics, curry leaves, pandan, coconut milk, and souring agents until dark, tender, and deeply flavored. It is commonly served as a main dish with steamed rice in everyday home meals.";
