"recipe.ma_meskouta.drink.body" = "A lightly sweet white such as Muscat complements the bright orange aroma and soft crumb without tasting sharp. For a non-alcoholic option, serve Moroccan mint tea or a glass of fresh orange-infused sparkling water.";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.drink.summary" = "Sweet wine (Muscat)";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.info" = "Meskouta is a classic Moroccan everyday cake, often orange-scented, mixed quickly in one bowl and baked until golden for a tender, lightly crumbed slice. It is commonly served at tea time, especially with mint tea, and enjoyed plain or simply with the natural citrus aroma from juice and zest.";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.info.summary" = "Orange tea-time cake";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.name" = "Meskouta";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.step1.body" = "Heat the oven and set a rack in the middle. Grease the cake pan with %i10 and dust with %i11, tapping out the excess.";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.step1.title" = "Prepare oven and pan";
"recipe.ma_meskouta.step2.body" = "In a mixing bowl, whisk %i1 with %i2 until well blended and slightly lighter. Whisk in %i3, %i4, %i5, and %i6 until smooth.";
