"recipe.ma_pastilla.drink.body" = "An aromatic white like Viognier or a lightly oaked Chardonnay complements the saffron, cinnamon, and buttery pastry while standing up to the rich filling. For a non-alcoholic option, serve Moroccan mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.ma_pastilla.drink.summary" = "White wine (Viognier)";
"recipe.ma_pastilla.info" = "Moroccan pastilla is a celebrated festive pie of spiced chicken cooked with onions, saffron, and warm aromatics, combined with a rich egg-onion sauce and a sweet, crunchy layer of almonds scented with cinnamon. The filling is wrapped in delicate warqa pastry, baked until deeply golden and crisp, then finished with a classic dusting of powdered sugar and cinnamon for its signature sweet-savory contrast.";
"recipe.ma_pastilla.info.summary" = "Festive chicken pie";
"recipe.ma_pastilla.name" = "Chicken pastilla";
