"recipe.ma_tagine_lamb_prunes.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied red such as Grenache or Syrah pairs well with the lamb richness and the warm cinnamon-prune sweetness. For a non-alcoholic option, serve Moroccan mint tea or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.ma_tagine_lamb_prunes.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Grenache)";
"recipe.ma_tagine_lamb_prunes.info" = "Moroccan lamb tagine with prunes is a classic sweet-savory dish where lamb is slowly braised with onions, saffron, ginger, and cinnamon until meltingly tender, then topped with prunes glazed in honey and cinnamon and finished with almonds. It is traditionally served for celebrations and family meals, brought to the table in the tagine and eaten with Moroccan khobz to scoop up the rich sauce and fruit.";
"recipe.ma_tagine_lamb_prunes.info.summary" = "Sweet-savory lamb tagine";
