"recipe.mm_mohinga.drink.body" = "Mohinga is traditionally paired with tea rather than wine, but a light aromatic white such as Riesling can work with the herbal fish broth. Non-alcoholic pairing: hot Burmese green tea.";
"recipe.mm_mohinga.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.mm_mohinga.info" = "Mohinga is a traditional Myanmar rice noodle soup with a fragrant fish broth thickened lightly with toasted chickpea flour and scented with lemongrass, garlic, and ginger. It is widely eaten for breakfast and also served throughout the day with rice noodles, boiled egg, lime, herbs, and crunchy fritters.";
"recipe.mm_mohinga.info.summary" = "Fish noodle soup";
"recipe.mm_mohinga.name" = "Mohinga";
