"recipe.mm_sanwin_makin.drink.body" = "Sanwin makin is traditionally served with Burmese tea rather than wine, and plain green tea balances its rich sweetness. Non-alcoholic pairing: hot Burmese green tea.";
"recipe.mm_sanwin_makin.drink.summary" = "Green tea";
"recipe.mm_sanwin_makin.info" = "Sanwin makin is a traditional Myanmar semolina cake dessert made with semolina, coconut milk, butter, eggs, and sugar, then baked until golden and topped with seeds. It is commonly prepared for donation feasts, family gatherings, and tea-time, and is served cut into small squares.";
