"recipe.mu_civet_de_cerf.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied red such as Syrah or Grenache matches the stew’s depth and gentle acidity from the marinade. If you want something fresher, a light red served slightly chilled also works. Non-alcoholic pairing: sparkling water with lemon or chilled hibiscus tea.";
"recipe.mu_civet_de_cerf.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.mu_civet_de_cerf.info" = "Civet de cerf is a prized Mauritian Creole-style venison stew, traditionally marinated with aromatics and simmered slowly until deeply savory and tender. It is commonly served for family gatherings and festive meals, spooned over steamed rice and accompanied by simple lentils (grains) that soak up the rich sauce.";
