"recipe.mu_rougaille_saucisse.drink.body" = "A light to medium-bodied red such as Grenache or a young Syrah works well with the smoky sausage and tomato acidity. If you prefer white, a crisp Sauvignon Blanc can cut through the richness and match the chili. Non-alcoholic pairing: sparkling water with lemon or chilled ginger-lime tea.";
"recipe.mu_rougaille_saucisse.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Grenache)";
"recipe.mu_rougaille_saucisse.info" = "Rougaille saucisse is a classic Mauritian Creole comfort dish of smoked sausages simmered in a punchy tomato sauce with onion, garlic, ginger, thyme, curry leaves, and chili. It is traditionally eaten as a full plate with steamed rice and a simple pot of lentils (grains), with piment crazé on the side for extra heat and sharpness.";
"recipe.mu_rougaille_saucisse.info.summary" = "Tomato sausage rougaille";
