"recipe.mu_vindaye_poisson.drink.body" = "Choose a zesty white like dry Riesling or Sauvignon Blanc to match the vinegar tang and mustard heat. If you prefer red, go for a very light, chilled red with low tannins. Non-alcoholic pairing: sparkling water with lime or chilled ginger tea.";
"recipe.mu_vindaye_poisson.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.mu_vindaye_poisson.info" = "Mauritian vindaye poisson is a tangy, mustard-forward fish pickle where fried fish is coated in a warm mixture of mustard seeds, turmeric, garlic, ginger, onions, and vinegar, then left to cure so the flavors sharpen and deepen. It is traditionally served at room temperature or slightly chilled, often as part of a meal spread or as a robust snack with crusty bread to mop up the spiced vinegar dressing.";
"recipe.mu_vindaye_poisson.info.summary" = "Mustard fish pickle";
