"recipe.mu_vindaye_poulpe.info" = "Mauritian vindaye poulpe is a tangy mustard-and-vinegar preparation where tender cooked octopus is coated in a warm mix of mustard seeds, turmeric, fenugreek, onions, garlic, ginger, and chili, then left to cure so the flavors sharpen and deepen. It is typically served at room temperature or slightly chilled as part of a Mauritian table or as a robust snack, commonly accompanied by crusty bread to soak up the spiced vinegar dressing.";
