"recipe.ng_afang_soup.drink.body" = "A light to medium-bodied red like Grenache (or a fruity, low-tannin blend) pairs well with palm oil richness and smoked fish without clashing with pepper heat. If you prefer white, a dry Riesling can work with the aromatic bitterness of the greens. Non-alcoholic pairing: chilled zobo (hibiscus) or sparkling water with lime.";
