"recipe.ng_ogbono_soup.drink.body" = "A dry Riesling or crisp Chenin Blanc balances the palm oil richness and pepper heat while staying refreshing. If you prefer red, choose a light, low-tannin red served slightly chilled. Non-alcoholic pairing: chilled zobo (hibiscus) or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.ng_ogbono_soup.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.ng_ogbono_soup.info" = "Ogbono soup is a classic Nigerian draw soup made by cooking ground wild mango seeds into a glossy, stretchy base enriched with palm oil, crayfish, pepper, and a robust assortment of meats and fish, then finished with leafy greens. It is traditionally served thick and hot as a main course with eba, used to scoop up the rich, elastic soup.";
"recipe.ng_ogbono_soup.info.summary" = "Draw soup classic";
