"recipe.ng_yam_porridge.info" = "Yam porridge, known as asaro, is a comforting Nigerian one-pot dish of yam cooked down with a rich pepper-tomato base, palm oil, crayfish, and fish until creamy with small chunks still intact. It is traditionally eaten hot as a satisfying main meal, often served with fried ripe plantain on the side to balance the savory, peppery porridge.";
