"recipe.nl_stamppot_boerenkool_met_worst.drink.body" = "Pair with a malty lager or amber beer that matches the smoky sausage and rich mash. A dry white such as Sauvignon Blanc can also work to cut through the fat. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water or a crisp apple spritz.";
"recipe.nl_stamppot_boerenkool_met_worst.drink.summary" = "Beer (Lager)";
"recipe.nl_stamppot_boerenkool_met_worst.info" = "Stamppot boerenkool is a traditional Dutch winter main of potatoes mashed with curly kale that wilts and softens during cooking, enriched with butter and milk for a thick, comforting texture. It is served piping hot with smoked sausage and crispy smoked bacon, making it a classic cold-weather meal found in Dutch home kitchens.";
