"recipe.no_farikal.info" = "Farikal is Norway’s national dish, a deeply traditional autumn stew of bone-in lamb or mutton layered with cabbage, whole black pepper, salt, and a little water, then simmered until meltingly tender. It is served very hot as a hearty family meal, traditionally with boiled potatoes.";
"recipe.no_farikal.info.summary" = "Norwegian lamb and cabbage";
