"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.drink.body" = "A crisp Sauvignon Blanc cuts through the richness and suits the shellfish well. A light lager is also a good match. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or hot black tea.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.drink.summary" = "White wine (Sauvignon)";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.info" = "New Zealand pāua fritters are a coastal classic made by mincing or finely chopping pāua, then mixing it with a small amount of onion, cream, egg, and flour before pan-frying. They are served hot with lemon and slices of buttered white bread, letting the shellfish remain the focus.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.info.summary" = "Classic pāua fritter";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.name" = "Pāua fritter";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step1.body" = "Trim the %i1, then pound it to tenderise. Finely chop or mince it until the pieces are small but still textured.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step1.title" = "Prepare the pāua";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step2.body" = "Finely chop the %i2, cut the %i10 into wedges, and butter the %i11 with %i12 so it is ready for serving.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step2.title" = "Prepare the other ingredients";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step3.body" = "Combine the pāua, onion, %i3, %i4, %i5, %i6, and %i7 in a bowl and mix until evenly bound.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step3.title" = "Make the fritter mixture";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step4.body" = "Heat the frying pan with %i8 and %i9 until hot and the butter is foaming.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step4.title" = "Heat the pan";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step5.body" = "Spoon the mixture into the pan as fritters and cook gently until the underside is set and lightly golden.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step5.title" = "Cook the first side";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step6.body" = "Turn the fritters carefully and cook until just firm and cooked through, taking care not to overcook the pāua.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step6.title" = "Turn and finish cooking";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step7.body" = "Serve the fritters hot with lemon wedges and slices of buttered white bread.";
"recipe.nz_paua_fritter.step7.title" = "Serve traditionally";
