"recipe.pe_rocoto_relleno.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied Tempranillo or Garnacha to handle the spice and savory filling. A crisp lager also pairs well with the heat. For a non-alcoholic option, serve chicha morada or a cold lime soda.";
"recipe.pe_rocoto_relleno.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Tempranillo)";
"recipe.pe_rocoto_relleno.info" = "Rocoto Relleno is the signature dish of Arequipa: spicy rocoto peppers are carefully de-seeded and parboiled to tame the heat, then stuffed with a savory picadillo of beef, onion, garlic, peanuts, raisins, and spices, topped with fresh cheese, and baked until bubbling. It is traditionally served with pastel de papa, a layered potato gratin baked alongside or served on the same plate.";
"recipe.pe_rocoto_relleno.info.summary" = "Stuffed spicy rocoto";
