"recipe.pe_seco_de_cordero.drink.body" = "Pair with a structured Cabernet Sauvignon or a medium-bodied Malbec to stand up to the lamb and herbal cilantro sauce. A dark lager also complements the beer-braised flavors. For a non-alcoholic option, serve chicha morada or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.pe_seco_de_cordero.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Cabernet Sauvignon)";
"recipe.pe_seco_de_cordero.info" = "Seco de Cordero is a classic Peruvian stew of lamb braised until tender in a vivid cilantro-based sauce with ají amarillo, garlic, and spices, enriched with dark beer and finished with peas. It is traditionally served with white rice and can be accompanied by yuca or potatoes depending on the region, but the essential pairing is rice to soak up the herbaceous sauce.";
