"recipe.pe_tacu_tacu.drink.body" = "Pair with a juicy Malbec or a medium-bodied Tempranillo to match the seared beef and savory sauce. A crisp lager also pairs well with the browned crust. For a non-alcoholic option, serve chicha morada or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.pe_tacu_tacu.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Malbec)";
"recipe.pe_tacu_tacu.info" = "Tacu Tacu is a classic Afro-Peruvian dish made by pan-frying a mixture of cooked rice and canary beans seasoned with garlic and ají amarillo until it forms a thick cake with a crisp, browned crust. It is traditionally served topped with lomo saltado-style sautéed beef in a savory tomato-onion sauce, making it a hearty main course with contrasting textures.";
