"recipe.ph_adobo.drink.body" = "A light red wine such as Pinot Noir pairs well with the savory, tangy braise without overpowering it. A pale lager is also a classic match. For a non-alcoholic option, serve calamansi juice or iced black tea.";
"recipe.ph_adobo.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.ph_adobo.info" = "Filipino adobo is a traditional braised dish of pork simmered with vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, bay leaves, and black peppercorns until deeply savory and glossy. It is a staple home-cooked meal across the Philippines and is most commonly served hot with steamed rice.";
