"recipe.ph_bicol_express.drink.body" = "An aromatic white wine such as off-dry Riesling pairs well with the spicy chilies and rich coconut sauce. A pale lager is also a classic match for the heat. For a non-alcoholic option, serve calamansi juice or iced tea.";
"recipe.ph_bicol_express.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.ph_bicol_express.info" = "Bicol Express is a traditional Filipino pork dish from the Bicol style of cooking, made by simmering pork with coconut milk, coconut cream, shrimp paste, and chilies until rich, spicy, and savory. It is commonly served hot as a main dish with steamed rice and is known for its bold heat and creamy sauce.";
