"recipe.pl_makowiec.drink.body" = "Pair with a lightly sweet dessert wine such as late-harvest Riesling to match the honeyed poppy filling, or a glass of semi-sweet sparkling wine for contrast. A dark, smooth porter can also complement the nutty poppy notes. Non-alcoholic option: black tea with lemon or coffee with milk.";
"recipe.pl_makowiec.drink.summary" = "Dessert wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.pl_makowiec.info" = "Makowiec is a traditional Polish yeast-raised roulade filled with a rich, fragrant poppy-seed paste cooked with milk, butter, and honey, then mixed with raisins and walnuts. The rolled loaf is proofed, baked until golden, and finished with a simple lemon icing that sets into a thin glaze. It is most closely associated with Christmas and Easter tables, served in neat slices with tea or coffee.";
"recipe.pl_makowiec.info.summary" = "Holiday poppy roulade";
"recipe.pl_makowiec.name" = "Poppy seed roll";
