"recipe.pl_pierogi_ruskie.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp dry white such as Riesling or Grüner Veltliner to balance the buttery onions and rich filling. A clean pilsner-style lager also fits well with the dumplings. Non-alcoholic option: cold kefir or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.pl_pierogi_ruskie.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.pl_pierogi_ruskie.info" = "Pierogi ruskie are classic Polish dumplings with a tender dough wrapped around a savory filling of mashed potatoes, farmer’s cheese, and fried onion, then boiled until they float and served hot. Traditionally they are finished with butter and golden fried onions, and often a spoon of sour cream, making a comforting everyday meal across Poland.";
