"recipe.pl_placek_po_wegiersku.drink.body" = "Pair with a medium-bodied, low-tannin dry red such as Pinot Noir to match the paprika and tender pork without overpowering the potato pancake. A malty amber lager also works well with the fried pancake and stew. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon or unsweetened black tea.";
"recipe.pl_placek_po_wegiersku.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.pl_placek_po_wegiersku.info" = "Placek po węgiersku is a beloved Polish comfort dish: a large, crisp potato pancake served under a rich, paprika-scented meat goulash thickened to a silky gravy with onions, peppers, and warming spices. It’s a popular restaurant classic and a hearty home meal, often finished with a spoon of sour cream to balance the savory sauce.";
