"recipe.pl_placki_ziemniaczane.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp dry white such as Riesling or Grüner Veltliner to cut through the fried richness and complement the tangy sour cream. A clean pilsner-style lager is also a natural match. Non-alcoholic option: kefir or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.pl_placki_ziemniaczane.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.pl_placki_ziemniaczane.info" = "Placki ziemniaczane are classic Polish potato pancakes: grated potatoes and onion bound with egg and a little flour, fried in hot fat until crisp and deeply golden. Traditionally they are served simply with a spoon of sour cream, making a comforting meal or supper that’s popular across Poland.";
"recipe.pl_placki_ziemniaczane.info.summary" = "Golden potato pancakes";
