"recipe.pl_ryba_po_grecku.drink.body" = "Pair with a crisp dry white such as Riesling or Grüner Veltliner to balance the tomato and gently sweet vegetables. A light lager also works well with the fried fish and saucy vegetables. Non-alcoholic option: sparkling water with lemon or unsweetened black tea.";
"recipe.pl_ryba_po_grecku.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.pl_ryba_po_grecku.info" = "Ryba po grecku is a traditional Polish dish of fried white fish covered with a sweet-savory tangle of grated root vegetables and onions stewed in a tomato sauce with bay leaf and allspice. Commonly prepared for Wigilia and family gatherings, it is typically made ahead so the flavors meld, then served cold or at cool room temperature as a hearty fish course.";
"recipe.pl_ryba_po_grecku.info.summary" = "Wigilia fish course";
"recipe.pl_ryba_po_grecku.name" = "Fish in tomato sauce";
