"recipe.pl_sernik.drink.body" = "Pair with a lightly sweet dessert wine such as late-harvest Riesling that matches the tangy cheese and vanilla without cloying. A darker, smooth porter can also complement the buttery crust. Non-alcoholic option: black tea with lemon or coffee with milk.";
"recipe.pl_sernik.drink.summary" = "Sweet wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.pl_sernik.info" = "Sernik krakowski is a traditional Polish baked cheesecake made with twaróg (farmer’s cheese), enriched with butter and eggs, lightly scented with vanilla and lemon, and baked on a buttery shortcrust base with a characteristic lattice top. It is cooled and chilled so the filling sets into a dense yet creamy slice, then finished simply with powdered sugar, and commonly served with coffee or tea at family gatherings and holidays.";
"recipe.pl_sernik.info.summary" = "Kraków baked cheesecake";
"recipe.pl_sernik.name" = "Baked cheesecake";
