"recipe.se_kalops.drink.body" = "A soft red such as Cotes du Rhone works well with the slow-cooked beef and warm spice. A dark lager is also a good match. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water or lightly sweetened lingonberry drink.";
"recipe.se_kalops.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Côtes du Rhône)";
"recipe.se_kalops.info" = "Kalops is a traditional Swedish beef stew from the husmanskost repertoire, slowly simmered with onion, carrot, bay leaf, and whole allspice until the meat is very tender and the broth turns rich and silky. It is classically served hot with boiled potatoes and pickled beetroot, especially as a hearty family meal in colder weather.";
"recipe.se_kalops.info.summary" = "Swedish beef stew";
