"recipe.sy_mabroumeh.drink.body" = "A floral Muscat or late-harvest Riesling complements the orange blossom syrup and buttery pastry. For a non-alcoholic option, serve hot black tea with mint or a chilled rosewater lemonade.";
"recipe.sy_mabroumeh.drink.summary" = "Dessert wine (Muscat)";
"recipe.sy_mabroumeh.info" = "Mabroumeh is a traditional Syrian pastry made from buttery shredded kataifi dough rolled around mild, stretchy cheese, baked until crisp and deeply golden, then soaked with fragrant sugar syrup and topped with pistachios. It is served warm or at room temperature for gatherings and celebrations, prized for its crunchy exterior, creamy center, and perfumed sweetness.";
