"recipe.sy_maqluba.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied Syrah or Grenache works well with the warm spices and savory chicken, while a soft Merlot can also fit. For a non-alcoholic option, serve ayran or a cucumber-mint yogurt drink alongside.";
"recipe.sy_maqluba.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.sy_maqluba.info" = "Maqluba is a traditional Syrian upside-down pot dish of spiced chicken, fried vegetables, and fragrant rice cooked together, then dramatically flipped onto a platter to reveal a layered dome. It is typically served family-style with a cool garlic yogurt-cucumber side that balances the warm spices and rich vegetables.";
