"recipe.tr_icli_kofte.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied Syrah or a fruit-forward Grenache pairs with the warm spices and fried crust without overpowering the filling. For a non-alcoholic option, serve ayran or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.tr_icli_kofte.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.tr_icli_kofte.info" = "İçli Köfte is a traditional Turkish dish of bulgur-and-semolina shells filled with spiced minced meat, onions, and walnuts, shaped into torpedoes and fried until crisp. It is served hot as a hearty main or substantial mezze, typically accompanied by lemon wedges and simple salad greens.";
"recipe.tr_icli_kofte.info.summary" = "Crisp stuffed croquettes";
"recipe.tr_icli_kofte.name" = "İçli köfte";
