"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied Syrah or Grenache pairs with the rich roasted lamb and savory juices, while a structured Tempranillo can also work. For a non-alcoholic option, serve ayran or sparkling water with lemon.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.info" = "Kuzu Tandır is a traditional Turkish dish of lamb slow-roasted until meltingly tender, then served with its juices and often paired with buttery rice pilaf to soak up the rich drippings. It is a celebratory main course, typically cooked low and slow so the meat becomes soft enough to pull apart.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.info.summary" = "Slow-roasted lamb feast";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.name" = "Lamb tandır";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step1.body" = "Crush %i2 and rub it over %i1 with %i3, %i6, %i7, %i4, and %i5.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step1.title" = "Season the lamb";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step2.body" = "Let the seasoned lamb rest so the flavors penetrate.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step2.title" = "Rest to marinate";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step3.body" = "Place the lamb in a roasting pan, add %i8, cover tightly, and roast low and slow until very tender.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step3.title" = "Slow roast covered";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step4.body" = "Uncover and roast until the surface is browned and the juices reduce slightly.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step4.title" = "Brown for color";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step5.body" = "Rinse %i9 until the water runs mostly clear, then drain well.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step5.title" = "Rinse the rice";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step6.body" = "Melt %i11, toast %i10 until golden, then add the rice and stir to coat.";
"recipe.tr_kuzu_tandir.step6.title" = "Toast vermicelli and coat rice";
