"recipe.tw_lu_rou_fan.drink.body" = "A light, low-tannin red such as Pinot Noir works with the sweet-savory braise without overwhelming it. For a non-alcoholic option, serve hot oolong tea or unsweetened barley tea.";
"recipe.tw_lu_rou_fan.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.tw_lu_rou_fan.info" = "Lu Rou Fan is a traditional Taiwanese comfort dish of finely cut pork belly slowly braised with soy sauce, rice wine, aromatics, and spices until glossy and rich, then spooned over steamed rice. It is commonly served as an everyday meal at homes and small eateries, often with braised egg and simple greens.";
"recipe.tw_lu_rou_fan.info.summary" = "Braised pork rice";
