"recipe.tw_oyster_omelet.drink.body" = "A light lager or pilsner balances the rich egg and briny oysters while refreshing the palate between bites. For a non-alcoholic option, serve hot oolong tea or chilled barley tea.";
"recipe.tw_oyster_omelet.drink.summary" = "Beer (Lager)";
"recipe.tw_oyster_omelet.info" = "Taiwanese oyster omelet is a classic night-market dish made with small oysters, eggs, and a sweet potato starch slurry that creates the signature chewy texture, cooked with leafy greens and topped with a sweet-savory sauce. It is typically served hot as a street snack or casual meal.";
