"recipe.ua_banosh.info" = "Banosh is a traditional Hutsul dish from western Ukraine made by cooking cornmeal in rich sour cream until thick and silky, then serving it topped with bryndza and pork cracklings. It is a rustic mountain meal traditionally eaten hot and is closely associated with the Carpathians and communal family cooking.";
