"recipe.ua_holubtsi.drink.body" = "A light to medium-bodied red wine such as Pinot Noir or Gamay pairs well with the sweet cabbage, savory filling, and tomato sauce. For a non-alcoholic pairing, serve kompot or hot black tea.";
"recipe.ua_holubtsi.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.ua_holubtsi.info" = "Ukrainian holubtsi are traditional cabbage rolls made with tender cabbage leaves filled with a savory mixture of pork, beef, rice, onion, and carrot, then baked in a tomato and sour cream sauce. They are a classic family and holiday dish in Ukrainian home cooking, served hot with extra sour cream at the table.";
