"recipe.us_md_crab_cakes.drink.body" = "A lightly oaked Chardonnay or a crisp pilsner works with the sweet crab and buttery crust without overpowering it. For a non-alcoholic option, serve sparkling water with lemon or an unsweetened iced tea to keep the flavors clean and refreshing.";
"recipe.us_md_crab_cakes.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.us_md_crab_cakes.info" = "Maryland crab cakes are a Chesapeake Bay classic built to showcase sweet blue crab with minimal filler, bound lightly with mayonnaise, egg, and a touch of mustard and seasoned with Old Bay. Traditionally formed into thick patties and pan-fried in butter until deeply golden, they’re served with lemon and tartar sauce for a bright, briny, rich plate that feels both coastal and celebratory.";
