"recipe.us_mi_detroit_style_pizza.drink.body" = "Juicy Barbera or a hoppy pale ale pairs well with pepperoni spice and caramelized cheese. For a non-alcoholic option, serve a cold cola or sparkling water with lemon to cut the richness.";
"recipe.us_mi_detroit_style_pizza.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Barbera)";
"recipe.us_mi_detroit_style_pizza.info" = "Detroit-style pizza is Michigan’s iconic rectangular pan pizza with a thick, airy crumb and a deeply crisp, caramelized edge created by cheese melted right up against the pan. It’s traditionally topped with pepperoni and finished with bold tomato sauce spooned or striped over the top after baking, giving the pie its signature look and balance of rich cheese, spicy meat, and bright sauce. Served hot from the pan, it’s a hearty, shareable slice that eats like comfort food with serious crunch.";
"recipe.us_mi_detroit_style_pizza.info.summary" = "Detroit pan pizza";
