"recipe.us_nm_green_chile_stew.drink.body" = "Off-dry Riesling or a crisp lager balances chile heat while staying refreshing alongside the savory pork and potatoes. For a non-alcoholic option, serve cold milk or sparkling water with lime to cool the palate.";
"recipe.us_nm_green_chile_stew.drink.summary" = "White wine (Riesling)";
"recipe.us_nm_green_chile_stew.info" = "New Mexico green chile stew is a Southwestern staple built around roasted Hatch-type green chiles, simmered with pork, potatoes, onion, and garlic into a warming, brothy stew with a gentle thickness from the starchy potatoes. The flavor is bright, earthy, and spicy, with the roasted chiles carrying the dish. Traditionally served hot with flour tortillas for dipping and scooping, it’s everyday comfort food across New Mexico.";
"recipe.us_nm_green_chile_stew.info.summary" = "Green chile stew";
"recipe.us_nm_green_chile_stew.name" = "Green chile stew";
