"recipe.us_sc_she_crab_soup.info" = "South Carolina she-crab soup is a Lowcountry classic: a rich, creamy crab soup traditionally made with blue crab, finished with crab roe for its signature flavor and color, and perfumed with a splash of dry sherry. Built on a gently simmered crab stock and a silky cream base, it’s served hot as a refined starter in coastal Carolina cooking, often with oyster crackers alongside.";
