"recipe.us_sc_shrimp_and_grits.drink.body" = "A lightly oaked Chardonnay or a crisp pilsner pairs with the buttery grits and smoky shrimp sauce without tasting harsh. For a non-alcoholic option, serve unsweetened iced tea or sparkling water with lemon to keep the meal bright.";
"recipe.us_sc_shrimp_and_grits.drink.summary" = "White wine (Chardonnay)";
"recipe.us_sc_shrimp_and_grits.info" = "South Carolina shrimp and grits is a Lowcountry classic pairing creamy stone-ground grits with sautéed shrimp in a savory bacon-rich sauce. The dish builds flavor by rendering bacon, cooking aromatics, and quickly cooking shrimp, then finishing with lemon and scallions before spooning everything over buttery, cheesy grits. Served hot and comforting, it’s a hallmark of coastal Carolina cooking that balances briny shrimp, smoky pork, and soft, rich grits.";
"recipe.us_sc_shrimp_and_grits.info.summary" = "Lowcountry shrimp grits";
"recipe.us_sc_shrimp_and_grits.name" = "Shrimp and grits";
