"recipe.uz_norin.drink.body" = "A light red such as Pinot Noir or a young Gamay can work with the rich meat and broth-coated noodles without overpowering them. A dry lager is also suitable. Non-alcoholic pairing: hot black tea is the traditional choice.";
"recipe.uz_norin.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Pinot Noir)";
"recipe.uz_norin.info" = "Norin is a traditional Uzbek festive dish, especially associated with Tashkent, made from very finely cut homemade noodles mixed with shredded boiled horse meat and enriched with broth and spices. It is commonly served on a platter for sharing, often garnished with slices of qazi and eaten with non and hot tea.";
"recipe.uz_norin.info.summary" = "Horse meat noodles";
"recipe.uz_norin.name" = "Norin";
"recipe.uz_norin.step1.body" = "Rub the %i1 with %i8, %i9, and %i10. Place it in a large pot, add %i3, and bring slowly to a boil while skimming the surface.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step1.title" = "Season and start broth";
"recipe.uz_norin.step10.body" = "Warm the %i12 briefly until soft and fragrant for serving.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step10.title" = "Warm bread";
"recipe.uz_norin.step11.body" = "Pile the norin onto a large platter, arrange the qazi slices on top, moisten lightly with broth, and serve with small bowls of hot broth and torn non bread.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step11.title" = "Serve";
"recipe.uz_norin.step2.body" = "Lower the heat and simmer gently until the meat becomes fully tender and a clear flavorful broth develops.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step2.title" = "Simmer meat";
"recipe.uz_norin.step3.body" = "Add the %i2 to the broth and cook gently until heated through and cooked, then remove it carefully and let it cool enough to slice later.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step3.title" = "Cook qazi";
"recipe.uz_norin.step4.body" = "Combine the %i4, %i5, %i7, and %i6 in a bowl and knead into a firm smooth dough. Cover and let it relax briefly.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step4.title" = "Make dough";
"recipe.uz_norin.step5.body" = "Let the dough rest so it rolls thinly without shrinking.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step5.title" = "Rest dough";
"recipe.uz_norin.step6.body" = "Roll the dough very thin, dust lightly with flour, and cut into broad sheets suitable for boiling.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step6.title" = "Roll and cut dough sheets";
"recipe.uz_norin.step7.body" = "Bring water to a boil in a pot and cook the dough sheets until just done, then drain and cool them enough to handle.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step7.title" = "Boil dough sheets";
"recipe.uz_norin.step8.body" = "Stack the cooked dough sheets and cut them into very thin short strips. Shred or finely slice the boiled horse meat. Slice the qazi into thin rounds.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step8.title" = "Slice noodles and meat finely";
"recipe.uz_norin.step9.body" = "Place the cut noodles and shredded meat in a large bowl, add a little hot broth and the %i11, and mix thoroughly so the noodles are glossy and evenly seasoned. Add black pepper and a little more cumin if needed.";
"recipe.uz_norin.step9.title" = "Season and mix norin";
