"recipe.uz_plov.drink.body" = "A medium-bodied red such as Syrah or Tempranillo pairs well with the rich lamb, sweet carrots, and fragrant cumin. A dry lager also works. Non-alcoholic pairing: hot black tea is the classic and most traditional choice.";
"recipe.uz_plov.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Syrah)";
"recipe.uz_plov.info" = "Uzbek Plov, also called osh or palov, is a traditional Uzbek rice dish cooked in a kazan with lamb, onions, carrots, spices, and garlic. It is a central celebratory dish served hot for family meals and gatherings, usually shared from a large platter with bread and tea.";
"recipe.uz_plov.info.summary" = "National rice plov";
"recipe.uz_plov.name" = "Plov";
"recipe.uz_plov.step1.body" = "Cut the %i1 into medium pieces. Slice the %i3. Cut the %i4 into long matchsticks. Rinse the %i5 several times until the water runs mostly clear, then drain. Trim the outer skin from the %i6 while keeping them whole.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step1.title" = "Prepare ingredients";
"recipe.uz_plov.step10.body" = "Turn off the heat and let the plov rest covered so the grains finish setting and the flavors meld.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step10.title" = "Rest plov";
"recipe.uz_plov.step11.body" = "Warm the %i11 briefly until soft and fragrant for serving.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step11.title" = "Warm bread";
"recipe.uz_plov.step12.body" = "Open the pot, loosen and mix the rice with the meat and carrots, then transfer to a large platter. Place the garlic bulbs on top and serve hot with torn non bread.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step12.title" = "Mix and serve";
"recipe.uz_plov.step2.body" = "Heat the kazan well and add the %i2. Add the lamb and brown deeply on all sides to build a rich base.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step2.title" = "Heat oil and brown lamb";
"recipe.uz_plov.step3.body" = "Add the onions to the lamb and cook until softened and golden.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step3.title" = "Cook onions";
"recipe.uz_plov.step4.body" = "Add the carrots, then cook until they soften slightly. Stir in most of the %i8, %i9, and %i10.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step4.title" = "Add carrots and spices";
"recipe.uz_plov.step5.body" = "Add %i7 to cover the meat and vegetables, bring to a simmer, and cook until the lamb begins to tenderize and the broth becomes aromatic.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step5.title" = "Make zirvak";
"recipe.uz_plov.step6.body" = "Nestle the whole garlic bulbs into the zirvak. Spread the drained rice evenly over the top in a flat layer without stirring into the meat.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step6.title" = "Add garlic and rice";
"recipe.uz_plov.step7.body" = "Pour in more water if needed so the rice can cook evenly, then simmer uncovered until the liquid is mostly absorbed and the rice is nearly tender.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step7.title" = "Cook rice uncovered";
"recipe.uz_plov.step8.body" = "Gather the rice gently toward the center, making a mound. Poke a few holes down through the rice to help steam circulate, then cover tightly.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step8.title" = "Steam setup";
"recipe.uz_plov.step9.body" = "Cook on very low heat until the rice is fully tender and fluffy and the lamb is tender.";
"recipe.uz_plov.step9.title" = "Steam covered";
