"recipe.ve_pabellon_criollo.drink.body" = "Serve with a light fruity red wine or a dry white wine that does not overpower the beef and beans. A light lager also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve papelón con limón or chilled black tea.";
"recipe.ve_pabellon_criollo.drink.summary" = "Red wine";
"recipe.ve_pabellon_criollo.info" = "Pabellón criollo is the traditional national dish of Venezuela, composed of carne mechada, black beans, white rice, and fried ripe plantain served together on one plate. It is a classic home-style meal with distinct components that balance savory, sweet, and earthy flavors, and it is traditionally served hot for lunch.";
