"recipe.vn_bo_luc_lac.drink.body" = "A light red wine such as Gamay or Pinot Noir pairs well with the savory caramelized beef. A crisp lager also works well. For a non-alcoholic option, serve unsweetened iced green tea or sparkling water with lime.";
"recipe.vn_bo_luc_lac.drink.summary" = "Red wine (Gamay)";
"recipe.vn_bo_luc_lac.info" = "Bo luc lac is a classic Vietnamese dish of marinated beef cubes quickly seared in a very hot wok or pan and shaken to brown the surface while keeping the center tender. It is traditionally served with lettuce, watercress, tomato, onion, steamed rice, and a lime-salt-pepper dipping sauce for a balanced meal.";
